## 5) RevenueCat + Google Play Setup (Do This Earlier Than You Think)

This is the slowest part because it touches multiple consoles.

### In Google Play Console
- [ ] Create the app (package name must match your Android build)
- [ ] Set up “Internal testing” track
- [ ] Enable Play App Signing
- [ ] Upload *an initial* AAB build (can be minimal) to unlock some product config flows
- [ ] Create subscription products / in-app products matching your iOS offering
  - [ ] Keep SKU naming consistent and documented
  - [ ] Match entitlement logic to what your app expects

### In RevenueCat
- [ ] Add Android app to your existing project
- [ ] Link Google Play credentials (service account JSON)
- [ ] Map Google Play products to RevenueCat offerings/entitlements
- [ ] Verify sandbox/test purchases from:
  - [ ] Internal testing track users
  - [ ] License testing accounts (as applicable)

**Milestone:** A test user can purchase premium on Android and your UI unlocks correctly.

