## 8) Play Store Listing + Compliance

### Store assets
- [ ] App icon (512x512)
- [ ] Feature graphic
- [ ] Phone screenshots (at least 2–8)
- [ ] Short description + full description
- [ ] Optional: promo video

### Compliance forms (don’t leave for last)
- [ ] Data safety form (be precise about what you collect/store)
- [ ] Privacy policy URL (must exist and match behavior)
- [ ] Content rating questionnaire
- [ ] Target audience and ads declarations (even if no ads)

**Milestone:** App is “ready to publish” with no missing policy items.

---

## 9) Launch Plan

### Suggested launch steps
- [ ] Release to Internal testing (same day you get a stable build)
- [ ] Fix high-severity issues discovered by testers
- [ ] Move to Closed testing (small group, 1–2 weeks)
- [ ] Production rollout:
  - [ ] Start with staged rollout (e.g., 10% → 50% → 100%)
  - [ ] Monitor crashes and purchase funnel

### Post-launch
- [ ] Add a weekly check of crash-free sessions and ANR rates
- [ ] Review RevenueCat dashboards for churn and purchase failures
- [ ] Plan v1.1 fixes quickly (Android will surface device-specific issues)

---

## 10) Known “Android Surprises” to Watch For

- WebView differences in keyboard/viewport behavior
- Background/resume state issues
- Password reset / email link flows breaking on native origins
- RevenueCat not unlocking due to misconfigured Play products/offerings
- versionCode not incrementing and blocking release uploads

---

## 11) Suggested Milestones

1. **M1:** App runs in emulator and on physical device (no auth)
2. **M2:** Auth + core workout tracking works end-to-end
3. **M3:** RevenueCat purchases + entitlements work in Internal testing
4. **M4:** Closed testing stable (crash monitoring added)
5. **M5:** Production release + staged rollout complete

